verbose_text: The clinical efficacy of therapeutic antibodies rely on two functional properties : first, the ability of the Fab regions to specifically recognize and bind the target; and second, the ability to induce different immune system effector mechanisms through interaction of the Fc region with Fc gamma receptors (FcgammaRs), the C1q component of complement and the neonatal receptor (FcRn).
evidence: interaction of the Fc region with Fc gamma receptors (FcgammaRs), the C1q component of complement and the neonatal receptor
